# Add PCEA Prescription Functionality

This plan details the changes required to parse PCEA network requests and implement the opening of PCEA prescriptions in the API and UI.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Based on the `pcea.pcapng` file, I have identified the following parameters for PCEA:
> - Route: `PCE`
> - Drug Code (`setDrgCode` & `OSTCode`): `ANES_TEST2`
>
> **Questions for User:**
> 1. Should the PCEA package include **Ropivacaine (ROP01)**, or only **Fentanyl (FEN02)** like PCA? (My analysis of the pcap did not find `ROP01`, so I plan to exclude it, similar to PCA).
> 2. What should the **Dose** be for Fentanyl in PCEA? (For PCA it's 1.0, for Painless it's 0.5. I plan to use 1.0 unless you specify otherwise).

## Proposed Changes

### Backend ([his_client.py](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_ver2/his_client.py))
#### [MODIFY] his_client.py(file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_ver2/his_client.py)
Update the [prescribe_package](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_ver2/his_client.py#81-222) function to handle `package_type == "PCEA"`:
- Remove Ropivacaine (`ROP01`) if not needed (based on user feedback).
- Set `Route` to `"PCE"`.
- Set `OSTCode` to `"ANES_TEST2"`.
- Set `sKey` to use `"ANES_TEST2"`.
- Set `UDOGivRoute` to `"PCE"`.
- Set `setDrgCode` to `"ANES_TEST2"`.
- Set `Dose` to 1.0 (or what user specifies).

### Frontend UI ([templates/index.html](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_ver2/templates/index.html))
#### [MODIFY] index.html(file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/AutoPrescribe_ver2/templates/index.html)
- Add a new button in the UI: `<button onclick="prescribe('PCEA')">開立 PCEA</button>`.
- Make sure it displays nicely next to the PCA and PAINLESS buttons.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Open the UI `http://localhost:3000`.
2. Select a patient.
3. Click the new "開立 PCEA" button.
4. Verify that the system successfully returns `Flow complete` and offers the `Controlled_Drug_Sheet_P022.pdf` for download.
5. Check backend logs to ensure HTTP 200 is returned from `IpoC11GSave` without errors.
